The river is a long, long strip
Of blue, down in the valley,     
And it flows with a heavy sigh,
And is thundering, roars and cries,
Clear above its soft agitations—
One could catch the echo’s smiles,
Splashing on the foam of the waves.

- James Russell Lowell
